# Availability Matcher

A Python tool for pairing people based on overlapping availability windows.
It uses weighted maximum‑cardinality matching to pair as many participants as possible
while reducing repeat pairings across cycles. It supports trio formation when pairing is not possible.

## Features

- Imports availability data from a CSV (exported from a Google Sheet)
- Computes overlapping time intervals between every pair of participants
- Uses a weighted maximum‑cardinality matching algorithm to:
    - Pair as many people as possible
    - Prefer fresh pairings by penalizing repeat matches
- Supports trio formation when three participants share a common overlap
- Outputs:
  - `matches.csv` — matched pairs with their overlapping times, includes unmatched participants
  - `past_matches.csv` — updated history of previous pairings

## Requirements

- Python 3.10+
- Dependencies listed in `requirements.txt`

